  "text": "The Rust compiler and Servo browser engine share code through the Stylo shared styling library. In servo/servo, the root Cargo.toml (lines 160, 178) declares external git dependencies on https://github.com/servo/stylo for the 'selectors' and 'style' crates. The components/layout/Cargo.toml and components/script/Cargo.toml both depend on these workspace crates. The layout/lib.rs file imports from the style module (lines 42-43) for WritingMode and ComputedValues, serving as the main entry point for the style system. The script/lib.rs file macro-uses stylo_atoms (line 21). In rust-lang/rust, the standard library proc_macro crate at library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs exports the proc_macro bridge public module (line 41), with the actual bridge interface defined in library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs. This bridge provides the RPC API for communicating between proc macro crates (like those used by Servo's build system) and the Rust compiler frontend. Servo does not directly depend on rust-lang/rust crates; rather, any Servo build scripts that use procedural macros would use the standard rust proc_macro bridge from the Rust standard library."
}

